/, a probability specific subjective subjunctive operator; used before an argument, usually a lepo clause, to give the accompanying predicate a subjunctive sense (PA). E.g., Mi hapci daumia lepo mi bragaiI am probably happy in the mental place where I am king (I would probably be happy if I were king).

/, a probability specific objective subjunctive operator; used before an argument, usually a lepo clause, to give the accompanying predicate a subjunctive sense (PA). /, as used in objective subjunctive sentences in which the causal condition is missing. E.g., Mi hapci dauvie baI would probably be happy (in some possible world/under some unspecified condition x). Cf. daumia ba for the suobjective sense of this subjunctive.
